formalText: He is anxious about what he is asking of from me on a lot of different levels.
Starts by saying, "I've been fairly anxious this week about a few different things.
I've been working on the same paper for the last couple months.
It's sort of been my big paper that I want to talk about and job interviews".
There is a sort of anxiety attached to "will I ever finish this"

He is also not sure if he wants to have children with Tanya but she is pregnant. Talked for awhile about what pregnancy and childbirth means to him. He has talked a lot to Tanya about her thoughts too
He expresses that they have had a hard time in their relationship talking about intimate things and have a skewed relationship of a lot of negative thoughts.
He has been trying to finish his paper before he sends out applications, but he needs to both send out applications because he needs to have a job.
One of his sisters is pregnant right now, went into labor recently over the weekend.
He states, "I think I have the sense of that one of the ways that people get through life is by sharing the joys and their sorrows with people".
He says, "I like to help people.
That's where I think this sort of the idea that being aware of somebody else's troubles is an important thing"

He states, "there are some real similarities between her and her mother some of those are presumed genetic and some of those presumably I believe like angry person raised children and turns them into angry people"
